# Trust or Trap — Project Core

Phishing/scam prevention **simulation game**. Solo Windows dev, PowerShell terminal.

## Must Read Before Coding

- `docs/product-planning.md` — flow, 7 scenarios, endings
- `docs/technical-architecture.md` — stack, LLM/TTS rules, folders
- `docs/domain-glossary.md` — persona/scenario IDs, risk flags

## Non-Negotiables

1. **Scenario graph is source of truth** — LLM generates dialogue only, never new plot
2. **API keys server-only** — Claude/Typecast in `app/api/` only
3. **Teen scenarios: no voice** — text/image chat only
4. **Phone UI** — `PhoneFrame` → `HomeScreen` → app components (reuse across 7 scenarios)
5. **Structured LLM output** — JSON `{ message, sender, options[], risk_flags[] }`, no free text
6. **3 endings** — `safe` / `warn` / `danger` per scenario graph

## Default Stack

Next.js App Router · TypeScript · Tailwind · Zustand · Framer Motion · Zod

## When Implementing

| Task | Read |
|------|------|
| New scenario node | Skill: `add-scenario-node` |
| Phone UI | Skill: `phone-ui-component` + rule: `phone-ui.mdc` |
| API/streaming | Skill: `streaming-api-route` + rule: `api-routes.mdc` |
| UI changes | Skill: `visual-qa-testing` |
